@feng-tao I was just referring to a possible situation, even thought it's rare. The dependency among DAGs is not maintained in DB, so checking whether a DAG is depended by another one before removing/modifying it is hard to do.

If we're checking from a "trading-off" perspective, I would agree with your point, and this PR LGTM.

My another suggestion is really nit: `has_checked_existence` may be better than `has_check_existence`?

@ashb @feng-tao do you think we can close this or any further work is needed?

After this PR is closed, I'll resume on the `contrib/auth` modules cleaning.

Thanks!

@BasPH Something about this PR seems to make the tests fail reliably on the v1-10-test branch

https://travis-ci.org/apache/airflow/builds/491746735

The previous commit, of #4215, https://travis-ci.org/apache/airflow/builds/491746787 is passing the failing tests. Do you have any ideas? Have I messed up the cherry-pick, or is there an extra test dependency that I need to cherry-pick in that you know of?a
